<h1 id="classes">Classes</h1>
<p>You can now write classes in ES2015.</p>
<pre><code class="language-js">class Circle {
  constructor (radius) {
    this.radius = radius
  }
  getArea () {
    return Math.PI * 2 * this.radius
  }
}
</code></pre>
<p>Classes let you define your own object types. You create instances of them using <code>new</code>. These instances have functions called &quot;methods,&quot; such as <code>getArea()</code> here.</p>
<pre><code class="language-js">c = new Circle(20)
c.getArea() //=&gt; 125.66
</code></pre>
